@{
    Layout = "_ReferenceLayout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Architecture explainer";
}
<div class="architecture-reference">
    <header class="reference-page-heading"><div><p class="lab-eyebrow">Phase 18 · System map</p><h1>How an answer travels</h1><p>A readable reference for the existing application boundary—presentation, APIs, retrieval, and model services remain independently deployable.</p></div><span class="ui-badge ui-badge-success"><i></i>Reference only</span></header>
    <section class="architecture-flow" aria-labelledby="flow-title"><header><p class="lab-eyebrow">Request path</p><h2 id="flow-title">From learner question to cited answer</h2></header><ol><li><span>01</span><div><strong>MVC / Razor UI</strong><small>Session context and question</small></div></li><li><span>02</span><div><strong>Application API</strong><small>Auth, course rules, orchestration</small></div></li><li><span>03</span><div><strong>Retrieval service</strong><small>Relevant indexed chunks</small></div></li><li><span>04</span><div><strong>Configured LLM</strong><small>Grounded answer generation</small></div></li><li><span>05</span><div><strong>SignalR stream</strong><small>Tokens, citations, completion</small></div></li></ol></section>
    <div class="architecture-layers"><article><span class="layer-number">A</span><p class="lab-eyebrow">Experience layer</p><h2>ASP.NET Core presentation</h2><p>Razor Views and browser JavaScript own navigation, interaction states, responsive layout, and accessible feedback.</p><ul><li>Current application remains unchanged</li><li>UI lab runs as a separate project</li><li>Same-origin adapter is opt-in</li></ul></article><article><span class="layer-number">B</span><p class="lab-eyebrow">Application layer</p><h2>Contracts and orchestration</h2><p>Existing REST endpoints and the chat hub remain the source of truth for authentication, sessions, courses, and documents.</p><ul><li>No duplicated business logic in the lab</li><li>Authorization stays server-side</li><li>Fixture data is visibly identified</li></ul></article><article><span class="layer-number">C</span><p class="lab-eyebrow">Intelligence layer</p><h2>Retrieval and generation</h2><p>Document processing, embeddings, retrieval, and model calls are presented as observable stages rather than hidden magic.</p><ul><li>Citations preserve source context</li><li>Benchmarks measure quality changes</li><li>Failures return actionable states</li></ul></article></div>
    <aside class="architecture-boundary"><strong>Merge-safety boundary</strong><span>Everything shown here lives under <code>ui-ux-lab/</code>. The existing solution does not reference this project, so the current startup and API paths do not change.</span><a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">View lab contract →</a></aside>
    <section class="adapter-contract"><div><p class="lab-eyebrow">Phase 19 · Optional integration</p><h2>Fixture first, live by choice</h2><p>The lab never requires the existing app to render. Add <code>?mode=live</code> to opt into the same-origin proxy; if the REST check fails, the adapter returns to fixtures and labels the fallback.</p></div><dl><div><dt>REST base</dt><dd><code>/backend/api/</code></dd></div><div><dt>SignalR hub</dt><dd><code>/backend/chatHub</code></dd></div><div><dt>Existing app</dt><dd><code>localhost:5096</code></dd></div></dl><div class="adapter-actions"><a class="ui-button ui-button-secondary" asp-action="Chat">Open fixture</a><a class="ui-button ui-button-primary" asp-action="Chat" asp-route-mode="live">Try live mode</a></div></section>
</div>
